----------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
BTW since we are on the subject.  Here is a list from a grammar site of grammar myths. <br>
----------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Grammatical Myths <br>
Most people try hard to follow grammatical rules that don't exist, because their school teachers ignored the grammar texts they distributed to their students! What a waste of time and effort! <br>
<br>
Don't end a sentence with a preposition. Nonsense. Absolute, total, unequivocal baloney! Some sentences are just fine a preposition at the end, and other sentences cannot be written without a preposition at the end. <br>
<br>
Don't begin a sentence with &quot;and&quot; or &quot;but.&quot; Nothing wrong with it. <br>
<br>
Don't split an infinitive. Utter nonsense. Absolutely no basis in English linguistics (or Germanic for that matter, from which English is derived).  <br>
<br>
Don't Use Passive Voice. Passive voice has its uses, and banishing it creates more problems. The underlying problem is that many business and government writers use passive voice inappropriately. But banning it? We wouldn't ban kitchen knives because some people misuse them, and there's no justification for banning passive voice, either. <br>
<br>
Don't Use &quot;That.&quot; Some wizard in an authoritative government position got the foolish idea that the word that was bad writing, so he banished it in his agency. The result was some of the most muddled memos and reports that anyone could imagine. Granted, some constructions can omit that without clouding the meaning, but banishing all uses of the word is flat out stupid. <br>
<br>
All the major grammar books say these constructions are all right. If you don't believe us (like some incredulous people), look up the rules yourself.  <br>
<br>
Here's a realistic rule to follow: Don't waste your time on these phony rules. Pay attention to real grammatical rules instead.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=viresttaelwaggler>Virest TaelWaggler</A> at: 1/31/03 12:49:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sciddvicioussmt>sciddvicioussmt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#628CBC>(1/31/03 12:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=476.topic&index=100>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Gramar nazi's</span><hr size=1> mmmm ass hat <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=erradicatedthoughts>Erradicated Thoughts</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Riding the Planes</span><br>  Posts: 947<br> <font color=#628CBC>(1/31/03 1:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=476.topic&index=101>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Gramar nazi's</span><hr size=1> I will reiterate.<br>
